				<div itemprop="commentText" class='post entry-content '>
					<blockquote  class="ipsBlockquote" data-author="renatov" data-cid="1470705" data-time="1393386299"><p>Does XDebug offer this? Is there another debugger for PHP that has these features?</p></blockquote><br>XDebug itself doesn't provide any kind of interface for actually interacting with the script. That is the job of a third-party client like your text editor or IDE. On the XDebug website they <a href='http://xdebug.org/docs/remote' class='bbc_url' title='External link' rel='external'>have a list of clients</a> that will provide this functionality. In the list there is:<br><blockquote  class="ipsBlockquote"><p><a href='https://code.google.com/p/xdebugclient/' class='bbc_url' title='External link' rel='external'>XDebugClient</a> - Standalone Windows client.</p></blockquote><br>If you're not using windows, then look at the list for other possible clients. If you feel comfortable with a compiler, the xdebug source package includes a simple client you can compile and use.
					
